-- Renewable Energy's EETEK Seeking $120 Million From Polish IPO to Invest
-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i
-- 2010-09-24T11:09:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-24/renewable-energy-s-eetek-seeking-120-million-from-polish-ipo-to-invest.html
EETEK Pcl, a Cyprus-based
renewable-energy provider, plans to sell as much as 358 million
zloty ($120 million) of shares in a Polish initial public
offering to finance investments in central Europe.  EETEK will offer 9 million new shares and an additional 2.2
million shares owned by its sole owner, Dexia-FondElec Energy
Efficiency & Emission Reduction Fund, at a maximum price of 32
zloty each, the company said in an e-mailed statement today.  Institutional investors may place orders for shares in the
IPO by Oct. 4, it said. The company plans to start trade on the
Warsaw Stock Exchange by mid-October, according to the
statement.  Erste Group Bank AG, with headquarters in Vienna, and
Equilor Investment Ltd., a Budapest-based asset manager, have
been hired to conduct the share sale.  “The Warsaw bourse’s strong position and its role as a
regional financial hub” were behind the decision to list shares
in Poland, according to a company statement on Sept. 9  The Warsaw exchange, central Europe’s biggest stock market,
has attracted 14 companies to list shares on its main market
this year and a further 60 companies on the NewConnect market,
according to the bourse’s website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
